Ecological notes : common in all types of woodland especially where there is plenty of dead wood; old hedges; grassland with pingo pools; calcareous grassland; marginal vegetation by upland lake; fen; bog; water meadows and gravel pits. Reared from pupae in moss, from yellow larvae in rotten alder wood. v–ix.
